This is common for many classes and not specific to the skald. With the recent block/parry changes, players should explore the options of making trade offs to raise parry if they want more in the area of melee defense. <br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
The problem here is that there is no viable Skald spec with Parry over 25. With only 1.5 points and a spell line that simply can not be specced below 43, there isn't enough points left to get a meaningful defense *and* offense. And a high Parry rating serves no purpose on someone with a low weapon spec, as there simply is no point for said someone to go into melee range any more.<br>
<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
Alternate templates are a good thing. We don't want there to be one single &quot;best&quot; template, so we'd look at this as a positive. <br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Except this isn't an alternate template. ALL Skald templates are based on the &quot;Minimum 43 BS for the last speed, weapon spec as high as possible, leftover into parry&quot; paradigm. This is just the most extreme variant of it. It, however, shows that more and more skalds consider the BS line to be of limited value except for the speed song, and Parry to be useless ( as it doesn't bring any tangible benefit unless specced higher than most Skalds can afford to).<br>
<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
This is a change that affected all DAs. As far as the realm abilities, we'll be reviewing all the underperformers at some point in time, but have no plans to adjust the skald's specifically. <br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Disappointing. Very disappointing. And not only from a Skald's point of view. There are some very ugly imbalances in the whole Class RAs system.<br>
<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
This helps skald defense as well. While it makes it more difficult for everyone to attack targets with such defenses, it has no affect regarding skalds and &quot;softer&quot; targets. <br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Except, again, Skalds do not have any significant way to spec defensively. So the change widened the gulf between us and &quot;real&quot; melee classes, and nothing more.<br>
<br>
<br>
-----------------------------------------------------------<br>
Nice report. Feel free to keep pushing the defensive issue. But right now, we really want to proceed with caution when evaluating any changes to the classes defense. <br>
----------------------------------------------------------- <br>
<br>
By this, I understand that you feel that you have boosted (game wide) defense enough in relation to offense for now. However, the defense concerns of the Skald class predate the general changes made to the game to lengthen combat. And they haven't really been solved, we still have a short life span compared to similar classes. This would be acceptable if our offense still worked as it used to, but this is no longer the case. So the concerns remain.<br>
