<br>
Minstrel<br>
Can spec stealth<br>
Evade II<br>
9-sec instant stun @ lvl 40 songs<br>
AE Mezz<br>
70pt AA chant<br>
Can get dodger RA<br>
<br>
Paladin<br>
2.0x skill<br>
Plate armor<br>
Spec shield<br>
Combo resist chants<br>
AF resist chant<br>
Self AF buff<br>
<br>
Now lets consider that 100% of all other realms melee classes get 2x spec:<br>
<br>
Melee classes<br>
Blademaster - 2x<br>
Champion - 2x<br>
Hero - 2x<br>
Armsman - 2x<br>
Merc - 2x<br>
Paladin - 2x<br>
Reaver - 2x<br>
<br>
Only Midgard gets melee classes with 1.5x spec.  Savages, who get dual-wield for free with HtH, and Skalds that get, umm???<br>
<br>
Ok - now with that baseline, here's a few groups of suggestions on how to fix skalds:<br>
<br>
Plan A<br>
* 2x spec<br>
* Shield spec<br>
* Increase range on all group chants to 1500 or 2000<br>
<br>
This simultaneously improves skald offense and defense, as well as group support with access to shield slam.  I expect this would be the most controversial change - so I suspect the least likely to happen.<br>
<br>
Plan B<br>
* Combination resist chants - 3 resist types per chant, and add a melee resist chant (still not as good as AA aura or pbt - but better than nothing)  Combination resist chants at least on par with Paladin's. (paladin 3-resist chants add 10)<br>
* Add stun shout - as per minstrel<br>
* Improve damage on dd shouts or reduce reuse timer to 15 seconds (improving damage increases frontloading, reducing reuse timer helps damage output over time, so I suspect a more palatable change would be reducing the reuse timer)<br>
* give skalds evade 2<br>
* give skalds access to dodger RA<br>
* Increase range on all group chants to 1500 or 2000<br>
<br>
This would provide better class support, better damage output, and better survivability.  Paladins get combo resist chants so that seems reasonable.  A chant that added +10 or +15 to 3 resists might even be worth singing.  Reducing the reuse timer on shouts from 20 to 15 seconds would offer a small increase in total damage output.  Evade 2 and access to dodger might actually let skalds survive and have defenses on par with the Rogue-based Minstrel.  Adding a stun shout as per minstrel would help to improve the usefulness of the skalds battlesong line, and help skalds do one of their primary jobs - peeling melee's off of their casters.<br>
<br>
Plan C<br>
* Allow skalds to run 2 chants at the same time. <br>
* Combination resist chants - 3 resist types per chant, and add a melee resist chant (still not as good as AA aura or pbt - but better than nothing)  Combination resist chants at least on par with Paladin's. (paladin 3-resist chants add 10)<br>
* Add stun shout - as per minstrel<br>
* Increase range on all group chants to 1500 or 2000<br>
<br>
<br>
This would make the skald a much better support class, but wouldn't dramatically change skald survivability. (other than what resist chants would grant since having the ability to have 2 chants going would make it more likely that one of them could be resist)  This might make the skald approach the group supporting usefulness of minstrels or paladins. (although minstrel still far better due to SoS)<br>
<br>
And in general:<br>
FIX THE SKAL RA - its such a travesty it isn't even funny.  It costs more than BoF or SoS to buy and is so much less valuable its not even funny.  How about something like letting all a skalds chants go active for 30 seconds?  If they're too lazy to fix the skald RA, reduce its cost to something trivial like 3 points, or if that's even too much, put it on an incredibly short reuse timer.<br>
<br>
Just a few late night thoughts...<br>
